    "gallery_text": "Joseph Friedman\u2019s best-known invention is the flexible straw, but the range of his inventive activities encompassed writing implements, improvements to engines, and objects for personal care, including this sketch for a seemingly simple pocket brush. Friedman frequently sketched on loose scraps of paper\u2014he was especially fond of envelopes\u2014working out ideas and solving problems, as here, where he laid out the basic premise of his invention in very simple terms: \"Lays flat. Moves to vertical position to use. Case used as a handle. Brush does come out completely.\"",
